 Games featured some of the most spectacular venues we\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ve ever seen, from the fencing and taekwondo in the Grand Palais, to tennis at Roland Garros, to the equestrian and modern pentathlon at Versailles.\", \"from\": 1211, \"to\": 1419, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1350, \"end\": 1363, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Open\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.841963529937077e-18, \"text\": \"Roland Garros\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Open\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Open\"}, {\"begin\": 1372, \"end\": 1382, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\", \"score\": 0.9998515313831636, \"rank\": 0.00014849066302781333, \"text\": \"equestrian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Games\", \"from\": 1211, \"to\": 1220}, {\"ngram\": \"the most spectacular venues\", \"from\": 1238, \"to\": 1265}, {\"ngram\": \"we\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ve\", \"from\": 1266, \"to\": 1273}, {\"ngram\": \"the fencing\", \"from\": 1290, \"to\": 1301}, {\"ngram\": \"taekwondo\", \"from\": 1306, \"to\": 1315}, {\"ngram\": \"the Grand Palais\", \"from\": 1319, \"to\": 1335}, {\"ngram\": \"Versailles\", \"from\": 1408, \"to\": 1418}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Then, of course, there\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s the Eiffel Tower, where they not only built a beach volleyball stadium, but had running and cycling races finishing right under the structure throughout the Games.\", \"from\": 1420, \"to\": 1610, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"course\", \"from\": 1429, \"to\": 1435}, {\"ngram\": \"a beach volleyball stadium\", \"from\": 1491, \"to\": 1517}, {\"ngram\": \"running and cycling races\", \"from\": 1527, \"to\": 1552}, {\"ngram\": \"the structure\", \"from\": 1575, \"to\": 1588}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1600, \"to\": 1609}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Put it this way: I have been following the Olympics for a very long time, and I couldn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t possibly tell you about any other venues for fencing and taekwondo.\", \"from\": 1611, \"to\": 1769, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1650, \"to\": 1662}, {\"ngram\": \"a very long time\", \"from\": 1667, \"to\": 1683}, {\"ngram\": \"any other venues\", \"from\": 1726, \"to\": 1742}, {\"ngram\": \"fencing\", \"from\": 1747, \"to\": 1754}, {\"ngram\": \"taekwondo\", \"from\": 1759, \"to\": 1768}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For Paris, I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll be able to.\", \"from\": 1770, \"to\": 1799, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1774, \"end\": 1779, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7950847303899912e-31, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So, it wasn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t all great for Paris.\", \"from\": 1801, \"to\": 1837, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1831, \"end\": 1836, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7950847303899912e-31, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The opening ceremony was held in boats along the famed river, which was a unique spin on an event that\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s typically steeped in tradition.\", \"from\": 1838, \"to\": 1976, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The opening ceremony\", \"from\": 1838, \"to\": 1858}, {\"ngram\": \"boats\", \"from\": 1871, \"to\": 1876}, {\"ngram\": \"the famed river\", \"from\": 1883, \"to\": 1898}, {\"ngram\": \"a unique spin\", \"from\": 1910, \"to\": 1923}, {\"ngram\": \"an event\", \"from\": 1927, \"to\": 1935}, {\"ngram\": \"tradition\", \"from\": 1966, \"to\": 1975}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was interesting, and memorable, but not the end of the story.\", \"from\": 1977, \"to\": 2041, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the story\", \"from\": 2031, \"to\": 2040}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The idea to put swimmers in the Seine deserves points for ambition, but the saga over whether the river was safe enough lingered over five events (three triathlons: men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s, women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s and mixed team; plus the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s and women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s open-water swims).\", \"from\": 2042, \"to\": 2291, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2074, \"end\": 2079, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5493913740412478e-22, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The idea\", \"from\": 2042, \"to\": 2050}, {\"ngram\": \"swimmers\", \"from\": 2058, \"to\": 2066}, {\"ngram\": \"points\", \"from\": 2089, \"to\": 2095}, {\"ngram\": \"ambition\", \"from\": 2100, \"to\": 2108}, {\"ngram\": \"the saga\", \"from\": 2114, \"to\": 2122}, {\"ngram\": \"the river\", \"from\": 2136, \"to\": 2145}, {\"ngram\": \"over five events\", \"from\": 2171, \"to\": 2187}, {\"ngram\": \"three triathlons\", \"from\": 2189, \"to\": 2205}, {\"ngram\": \"mixed team\", \"from\": 2230, \"to\": 2240}, {\"ngram\": \"the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s\", \"from\": 2247, \"to\": 2258}, {\"ngram\": \"open-water swims\", \"from\": 2273, \"to\": 2289}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There were rescheduled events and canceled training swims.One Dutch triathlete said, \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cSwimming in the Seine was disgusting.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Another \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cfelt and saw things that we shouldn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t think about.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d I also found it baffling that the IOC had no satisfying backup plan in case the triathlon would have had to be scrapped.\", \"from\": 2292, \"to\": 2609, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2354, \"end\": 2359, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.9999999978008418, \"rank\": 1.7917136912263905e-09, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}, {\"begin\": 2396, \"end\": 2401, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5493913740412478e-22, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 2523, \"end\": 2526, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1899487607855226e-64, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"There were rescheduled events\", \"from\": 2292, \"to\": 2321}, {\"ngram\": \"canceled training swims\", \"from\": 2326, \"to\": 2349}, {\"ngram\": \"disgusting.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d\", \"from\": 2406, \"to\": 2420}, {\"ngram\": \"Another\", \"from\": 2421, \"to\": 2428}, {\"ngram\": \"things\", \"from\": 2445, \"to\": 2451}, {\"ngram\": \"no satisfying backup plan\", \"from\": 2530, \"to\": 2555}, {\"ngram\": \"case\", \"from\": 2559, \"to\": 2563}, {\"ngram\": \"the triathlon\", \"from\": 2564, \"to\": 2577}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They would have simply turned the event into a duathlon (running and cycling) instead of finding another triathlon course literally anywhere in France.\", \"from\": 2610, \"to\": 2761, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2754, \"end\": 2760, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999993938119606, \"rank\": 4.43371171760885e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q